# Update a user by ID

Updates specific fields of the [`user`](user.md) object specified by the `id` parameter. Only the fields provided in the request body will be modified.

## URL

```shell
{server_url}/users/{id}
```

## Parameters

| Parameter name | Type | Description |
| -------------- | ------ | ------------ |
| `id` | number | The record ID of the user to update |

## Request headers

| Header name | Type | Required | Description |
| ----------- | ---- | -------- | ----------- |
| Content-Type | string | Yes | Must be `application/json` |

## Request body

Provide only the fields you want to update. All fields are optional.

```js

{
    "lastName": "string",
    "firstName": "string",
    "email": "string"
}
```

### Request body parameters

| Property name | Type | Description |
| ------------- | ---- | ----------- |
| `lastName` | string | The user's last name |
| `firstName` | string | The user's first name |
| `email` | string | The user's email address (must be valid email format) |

## Return body

```js
{
    "lastName": "Johnson",
    "firstName": "Ferdinand",
    "email": "f.johnson@example.com",
    "id": 1
}
```

Returns the complete updated user object with all fields.

## Return status

| Status value | Return status | Description |
| ------------- | ----------- | ----------- |
| 200 | Success | User updated successfully |
| 400 | Error | Invalid request body or email format |
| 404 | Error | Specified user record not found |
| ECONNREFUSED | N/A | Service is offline. Start the service and try again. |

## Example request

```shell
curl -X PATCH "{server_url}/users/1" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "lastName": "Johnson",
    "email": "f.johnson@example.com"
  }'
```
